description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to become part of a dynamic MSK outpatient service based at the Stanmore site at the Royal National Orthopaedic Hospital (RNOH) .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The RNOH is a national centre of excellence and the leading orthopaedic hospital in the UK with an international reputation for diagnosis, assessment and treatment of neuro-musculoskeletal conditions. This ranges from the most acute spinal cord injury, bone tumour and complex joint reconstruction to orthopaedic and specialist rehabilitation. This broad range of neuro-musculoskeletal services is unique within the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers the opportunity to develop highly advanced musculoskeletal skills and assess and treat a variety of complex patients with the confidence of being in a supportive team including Advanced Practitioners .The leadership opportunities include service development and staff training to a high level and evaluating service delivery using outcomes to ensure the highest of standards are maintained and innovative practice facilitated.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Therapy directorate has a strong research, education and innovation culture providing the successful candidate with many opportunities to be active in these areas alongside established strong training and academic links.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Helen Nafis, Clinical Specialist Physiotherapist on 020 8909 5820 or via helen.nafis@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
